⭐ Question 1 (Teamwork)
Tell me about a time you had to work with someone who was difficult or had a different working style than you. How did you handle it?
I was working with a coworker, we were in a van heading to a worksite
We stopped to get something to eat. 
Situation : When  we got back to the van we noticed we had a flat tire. 
I immediately said I will get the jack but my coworker said no we can’t touch that.
Task : We have to call for roadside assistance. I told him we have a spare it’s easy to change.
But he had a good point. He said what if we get hurt changing the tire. Our union or the company would not cover us because that was not part of our job. I still insisted that we can change it and save time and the company money but he had seniority and even if I did that did not authorize me to enlist him in changing the tire because it was not part of our job description. 
Action : We called roadside assistance and they came out and took care of it and we were on our way to our jobsite. 
Results : I wanted to go the extra mile but at the same time I put myself in a compromising position and I had to listen to my coworker to really understand the big picture and consequences that can happen and endanger our safety. 
