Polished Version (How You Could Say It in an Interview)
Here’s a tightened, professional version of your story:
I was traveling with a coworker to a jobsite when we stopped for food and came back to find a flat tire. My initial reaction was to grab the jack and change it ourselves so we could save time and money. However, my coworker pointed out that changing the tire wasn’t part of our job duties, and if we were injured, the company or union might not cover us.
After discussing it, I realized he was right — safety and policy needed to come first. We decided to call roadside assistance. Although it delayed us slightly, it ensured we stayed safe and compliant with company policy.
That experience taught me the importance of stepping back, listening to others, and considering the bigger picture instead of just reacting quickly. Now I always weigh safety and policy before taking action.
