🎯 Polished Interview Version
Here’s how you could deliver this confidently:
While working in a medical clinic, I roomed a patient and began taking their vital signs. After informing the doctor that the patient was ready, I realized that we had documented vitals under the wrong patient’s chart. Although we had asked for the patient’s name, we failed to verify a second identifier.
I immediately stopped the process, corrected the documentation, and ensured the correct patient was roomed and properly assessed before seeing the doctor.
That experience reinforced the importance of following full patient identification protocols every time. Afterward, I made it a personal standard to always use two identifiers, and the clinic later implemented clearer name-tag procedures to reduce the risk of similar errors.
It taught me that even small lapses in verification can have serious implications, and accountability means correcting mistakes quickly and improving systems moving forward.

